<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1704,2017]" lastBlockId="17.[151,1436,151,429]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="118" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,324,1704,1729]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">Redescription.</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[420,546,1705,1729]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" unit="mm" value="22.5" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="21.0">21–24 mm</quantity>
. Body oval, elongate; dorsal surface dark chestnut-brown, punctate. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[159,245,1740,1765]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 50" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[232,1365,244,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[173,1414,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 50. Phyllophaga schizorhina adult male. Pronotum, dorsal view (41), left antenna (42), right protarsal claw (43); right metatibia (44); distal appearance of abdomen, lateral view (45), dorsal view (46), ventral view (47); male genital capsule, lateral view (48 and 49), transversal view (50). (Figs. 48 – 50 after Morón 2003) Scale: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219008/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">
Fig. 
<number box="[216,245,1741,1765]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
) is wider than long the dorsal half, lateral margins irregular, crenulate. Clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[1209,1295,1740,1765]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 50" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[232,1365,244,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[173,1414,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 50. Phyllophaga schizorhina adult male. Pronotum, dorsal view (41), left antenna (42), right protarsal claw (43); right metatibia (44); distal appearance of abdomen, lateral view (45), dorsal view (46), ventral view (47); male genital capsule, lateral view (48 and 49), transversal view (50). (Figs. 48 – 50 after Morón 2003) Scale: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219008/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">
Fig. 
<number box="[1266,1295,1741,1765]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
) is bilobed, concave, with a raised margin. Antennae (
<figureCitation box="[626,708,1776,1801]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 50" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[232,1365,244,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[173,1414,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 50. Phyllophaga schizorhina adult male. Pronotum, dorsal view (41), left antenna (42), right protarsal claw (43); right metatibia (44); distal appearance of abdomen, lateral view (45), dorsal view (46), ventral view (47); male genital capsule, lateral view (48 and 49), transversal view (50). (Figs. 48 – 50 after Morón 2003) Scale: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219008/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">
Fig. 
<number box="[679,708,1777,1801]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
) have 
<number box="[785,813,1777,1801]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" value="10.0">10</number>
antennomeres with the antennal club as long as the six preceding antennomeres. Tarsal claws (
<figureCitation box="[590,671,1813,1838]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 50" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[232,1365,244,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[173,1414,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 50. Phyllophaga schizorhina adult male. Pronotum, dorsal view (41), left antenna (42), right protarsal claw (43); right metatibia (44); distal appearance of abdomen, lateral view (45), dorsal view (46), ventral view (47); male genital capsule, lateral view (48 and 49), transversal view (50). (Figs. 48 – 50 after Morón 2003) Scale: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219008/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">
Fig. 
<number box="[642,671,1813,1837]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" value="43.0">43</number>
</figureCitation>
) have a ventral tooth located next to the basal expansion. Metatibiae are long, wide, and flat (
<figureCitation box="[423,505,1848,1873]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 50" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[232,1365,244,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[173,1414,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 50. Phyllophaga schizorhina adult male. Pronotum, dorsal view (41), left antenna (42), right protarsal claw (43); right metatibia (44); distal appearance of abdomen, lateral view (45), dorsal view (46), ventral view (47); male genital capsule, lateral view (48 and 49), transversal view (50). (Figs. 48 – 50 after Morón 2003) Scale: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219008/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">
Fig. 
<number box="[475,505,1849,1873]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" value="44.0">44</number>
</figureCitation>
) with two typical spurs, of which the inner spur is shorter than the outer spur and is fused with the tibia; similarly, two toothed carinae in the mid and basal portion are present. The pygidial plate has minute setae on its ventral and frontal extremes (
<figureCitation box="[696,834,1920,1945]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 50" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[232,1365,244,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[173,1414,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 50. Phyllophaga schizorhina adult male. Pronotum, dorsal view (41), left antenna (42), right protarsal claw (43); right metatibia (44); distal appearance of abdomen, lateral view (45), dorsal view (46), ventral view (47); male genital capsule, lateral view (48 and 49), transversal view (50). (Figs. 48 – 50 after Morón 2003) Scale: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219008/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">
Figs. 
<number box="[759,834,1920,1945]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" value="46.0" valueMax="47.0" valueMin="45.0">45–47</number>
</figureCitation>
); also, anterior-distal punctures in the ventral position are present. The male genital structure (
<figureCitation box="[595,729,1957,1982]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 50" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[232,1365,244,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[173,1414,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 50. Phyllophaga schizorhina adult male. Pronotum, dorsal view (41), left antenna (42), right protarsal claw (43); right metatibia (44); distal appearance of abdomen, lateral view (45), dorsal view (46), ventral view (47); male genital capsule, lateral view (48 and 49), transversal view (50). (Figs. 48 – 50 after Morón 2003) Scale: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219008/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">
Figs. 
<number box="[658,729,1957,1982]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" value="49.0" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="48.0">48–50</number>
</figureCitation>
) is easily differentiable, the base of genital capsule has a short, sinuous distal margin and the dorsal basal margin is projected. Parameres are 1.3 times longer than the width of the base, finishing in a rounded apex. The ventral membrane of the genital capsule does not have sclerotized plates (
<figureCitation box="[159,299,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 50" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[232,1365,244,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[173,1414,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 50. Phyllophaga schizorhina adult male. Pronotum, dorsal view (41), left antenna (42), right protarsal claw (43); right metatibia (44); distal appearance of abdomen, lateral view (45), dorsal view (46), ventral view (47); male genital capsule, lateral view (48 and 49), transversal view (50). (Figs. 48 – 50 after Morón 2003) Scale: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219008/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
Figs. 
<number box="[224,299,188,212]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" value="48.5" valueMax="49.0" valueMin="48.0">48–49</number>
</figureCitation>
); the aedeagus is slightly asymmetric with a narrow, somewhat sclerotized, hook-shaped support at the apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
